# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only the WEBSITE is published to GitHub Pages. GitHub Pages republishes the
# whole repo on every build and caps the total site at ~1 GB. Everything outside
# Travel-Website/ (Icons Library ~672MB, Brain rules+scripts, archive, Hotel
# Research, shopping profile, scratch audit folders) is authoring material that
# lives on the shared Drive only — it must NEVER be published: it blows the 1 GB
# limit (failing every deploy with "Page build failed" / dur 0) and exposes
# private files on a public site.
#
# Whitelist strategy: ignore EVERY top-level entry, then re-include only the site
# and the two deploy files. Any NEW top-level folder a crib creates is auto-
# excluded — no maintenance needed. Files all stay on disk; this only controls
# what git tracks/publishes.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/*
!/.gitignore
!/.nojekyll
!/Travel-Website/
# CI: the Pages deploy workflow must be tracked (it gates deploys on guide validation).
# Only .github/ is re-included for tracking; it is NOT published to the site (the
# deploy job stages only Travel-Website/ + .nojekyll — see .github/workflows/deploy-pages.yml).
!/.github/

# Guide build scaffolding INSIDE the site tree. IMPORTANT: guide HTML serves its
# photos straight out of _build/assets/ (src="_build/assets/800px-*.jpg"), so that
# ONE subfolder IS published site content and must stay tracked. Everything else in
# _build/ (verification logs, build_state, raw full-size originals) is not served —
# ignore _build/ contents but re-include _build/assets/.
**/_build/*
!**/_build/assets/

# OS / editor cruft anywhere
**/.DS_Store
**/.fuse_hidden*
*.pyc
Travel-Website/Guides/Naples/naples_v1.html
Travel-Website/Guides/Victoria/victoria_v1.html
